All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary Exception Summary 
    Class Description
    AppContext
    Interface providing access to application-wide resources and values.
    Appointment
    Class representing an appointment, containing information about the appointment from the database or prepared for storage in the database.
    AppointmentController
    Controller for managing the windows that add and modify appointments.
    AppointmentDao
    DAO providing read/write access to appointments in the database, which it represents in the application as instances of Appointment.
    AppointmentDao.MonthTypeCount
    POJO for objects returned by getMonthTypeCounts() for the report of appointment counts by appointment month and type.
    AppointmentFilter
    Base class of filters for the appointments tab on the main window, also serving as a namespace for the different filters, implemented as subclasses.
    AppointmentFilter.Monthly
    Filter of appointments by month, showing one month at a time.
    AppointmentFilter.None
    Filter that does not filter at all, resulting in a display of all appointments.
    AppointmentFilter.Weekly
    Filter of appointments by week, showing one week at a time.
    AppointmentsByContact
    Report generating a table of appointments sorted by contact name, showing contact names in the first column, and replacing duplicate contact names with quotation marks to emphasize contact groupings.
    AppointmentsByMonthAndType
    Report generating a table of appointment counts for each combination of month and appointment type, sorted by month.
    AppointmentsController
    Manages the appointments tab on the main window.
    ColumnSpec<I>
    POJO for generically specifying a TableView column.
    ConfirmationDialog
    ConfirmationDialog is a class representing a confirmation dialog, which asks the user to confirm or cancel an operation.
    Contact
    POJO representing a contact, containing only information the application needs.
    ContactCache
    Cache of contacts pulled from the database.
    Controller
    The base class for all controllers.
    Country
    POJO representing a country, containing only information the application needs.
    CountryCache
    Cache of countries pulled from the database.
    Customer
    Class representing an customer, containing information about the customer from the database or prepared for storage in the database.
    CustomerController
    Controller for managing the windows that add and modify customers.
    CustomerDao
    DAO providing read/write access to customers in the database, which it represents in the application as instances of Customer.
    CustomerDao.CountryDivisionCount
    POJO for objects returned by getCountryDivisionCounts() for the report of customer counts by customer country and "first level division".
    CustomersByCountryAndDivision
    Report generating a table of customer counts for each combination of country and "first level division", sorted by country.
    CustomersController
    Manages the customers tab on the main window, which displays a table of all customers.
    Database
    Class representing the database and managing connections to the database.
    DatabaseException
    Exception representing an application-sanitized database error, including a user-readable message for explanation.
    DatabaseOperation<I>
    Abstract representation of an operation to add or modify a database item.
    Division
    POJO representing a "first level division" of a country, containing only information the application needs.
    DivisionCache
    Cache of country "first level divisions" pulled from the database.
    InformationDialog
    InformationDialog is a class representing an information dialog, which informs the user of an issue and waits for acknowledgement.
    InvalidArgException
    Exception reporting that a method was provided with an invalid argument.
    LoginController
    Manages the login form, displaying errors on failure to login, and launching MainController on successful login to show the main window.
    LoginLog
    Class representing the log file of user logins.
    LookupCache<I>
    Base class for caches of database items, used for lookups in the application.
    Main
    Main is the class representing the entire application.
    MainController
    Manages the main window that opens after logging in.
    ReadWriteDao<I extends WithID>
    Base class of DAOs that provide read and write access to a class of items in the database.
    Refreshable
    Interface for controllers that provide views of the database that may go stale due to activity outside the application.
    Report<I>
    Base class for reports shown on the reports tab of the main window.
    ReportsController
    Manages the reports tab on the main window, providing a drop-down menu for selecting the desired report, as well as a refresh button for updating the report to reflect the activity of other users.
    SceneHelper
    Class providing static methods that help with building scenes.
    TablePaneController<I extends WithID>
    Base class for a controller that manages a particular tab of the main window.
    User
    POJO representing a user and providing date and time formatting constants, which might be user-configurable in a more elaborate solution.
    UserDao
    DAO providing access to users in the database.
    WindowController
    Base class for all controllers that represent windows (having a stage), configuring the details of the window, including its modality.
    WithID
    Interface for model objects having accessors for an ID property.
